YENAGOA – Men of the Bayelsa State Police Command have arrested two suspects for alleged gun running in the state, following a tip-off. A statement on Saturday by the command’s Public Relations Officer, Asinim Butswat, said the suspects, identified as Seibo Dokubo and Boma Daniel, were nabbed at a brothel in Ayama, near Yenagoa, on Wednesday. It listed the items recovered from them as one Brownie Pistol loaded with 8.9mm ammunition, three expended 12.7mm ammunition, the sum of N2m and a vehicle without a number plate suspected to have been stolen. -Advertisement- The command claimed that the suspects “wanted to procure AK-47 rifles for kidnap purposes.” The statement read, “Operatives of the anti-kidnapping unit, Bayelsa State Command, while acting on a tip-off on 12th May, 2022 at about 1750 hours, bursted a gun running gang at a Brothel, at Ayama, Yenagoa Local Government Area. “The suspects one Seibo Dokubo ‘m’ 32 years, a native of Degema, Rivers State and one Boma Daniel ‘m’ 45 years a native of Patani, Delta State, wanted to procure AK-47 Rifles for Kidnap purposes. “One Brownie Pistol loaded with eight 9mm ammunition, three 12.7mm expended ammunition, sum of two million naira cash and a suspected stolen Toyota Hilux 2021 model without registration number, were recovered from the suspects. “The suspects are cooperating with Police in its investigation and will be charge to court at the conclusion of the investigation.”